title: Migrating the Spool DAO Treasury Smart Vault [SIP - 1.19]
description:
## Summary 📑

Transfer the 10 million DAI from the current treasury Smart Vault to a new one with increased yield.

## Proposal 📫

For the past X months the majority of treasury funds has been generating yield in its designated vault leveraging Aave, Compound, Convex (3pool), Curve (3pool), Harvest, Idle, and Yearn strategies. As the Curve strategy has decreased its yields and the exposure is equal due to Convex Finance, we propose to set up a new Treasury Smart Vault that has the Curve strategy removed and subsequently transfer the 10 million DAI into the newly created Smart Vault.

# Motivation 🔥

The not yet needed DAO treasury funds shall continue farming yield within the Spool protocol but with a potentially higher APY. With this vote Spool DAO should decide to set up a new, unincentivized, low-risk Spool, to raise the yield from currently ~$178,000 annually to ~$223,000. The additional $45,000 will benefit future development and enable further improvement of the Spool protocol and brand.

## Vote 🗳

With “Yes” you vote to set up a new Spool Treasury Smart Vault and transfer the balance of the current Treasury to it, with “No” you vote against this strategy.

 - `voting_period`: The period that is allowed for voting on this proposal. Increased to
   `FastTrackVotingPeriod` if too low.
 - `delay`: The number of block after voting has ended in approval and this should be
   enacted. This doesn't have a minimum amount.

 Emits `Started`.

title: RSP-1: Vote on BIP-30
description:
## Proposer

Root DAO Multisig

## RSP Process Note

Per the process outlined in the [RSP Process](https://docs.roottoken.org/governance/root-token/rdm-process#about-rsp-process), the Root DAO Multisig (RDM) will repost BIPs on the Root Stalk Proposals Snapshot page as RSPs.

## Links

* [BIP-30 Snapshot](https://snapshot.org/#/beanstalkdao.eth/proposal/0x724bbca47b55d42ec25f76c233846bdbbae1dd833618b938c84d58f53ffe7c3d)

## Quorum

An account's vote for a given RSP, or Voting Roots, is counted as the
minimum of its Roots between the beginning and end of the Voting Period.

Quorum is more than half of the total Voting Roots voting For, or about **87,842** Roots voting For based on the time of proposal.

## Voting Period

The Voting Period for RSP-1 ends 12 hours before the end of the Voting Period for BIP-30 in order to allow RDM Signers sufficient time to execute the vote.

## Proposal

We propose that the RDM executes the will of the Root DAO by voting on BIP-30 in accordance with the outcome of RSP-1. If RSP-1 does not pass, the RDM will not participate in the vote.

So, I would suggest to support the option is having insurance cover for user assets in stargate. Any user can pay a small premium to cover his/her assets in the pool.

This will help users stake/add liquidity  without much fear and arrest exodus of liquidity out of our system.

We are looking for funding to create 12 sign language based educational videos around the Synthetix community. These videos would be made by sign language interpreters and will be released every week.
description:
## Username 
sb_ksm

## Grant Description
Hi After going through the crypto youtube channels I found that there weren’t any tutorials that cater to the specially abled community, especially people who need sign language to operate. The reason why I bring this up is because I have a close family member who is specially abled and while he is eager to learn about crypto ecosystem, he couldn’t find anything that could help him learn even the basics. 

After discussing the whole issue with him I realised that there are plenty more like him who are looking to get into the crypto community but aren’t able to because of the lack of resources and the marginalisation of the specially abled community. It was then when we decided to connect with interpreters who could build some videos around this ecosystem based on the current available content.


## Overview
According to the World Report on Disability  by WHO from 2011, the most marginalised people when it comes to education are not the poor but rather people with special disabilities. Particularly in the crypto space, these folks are being widely excluded from even providing them the basics of crypto education.

Based on another report less than 1% of people with special disabilities are currently participating in the crypto space which I believe is a strong negative indication towards inclusivity. It’s our duty to include newcomers into this industry through educating them properly and while there will always be people that are not willing to put in the time, we’ve seen over and over again that there’s many that do want to learn more, but simply can’t find good educational sources to do so. 

In the USA currently sign language is the 4th most used language by numbers and most of the population that lies in this group comes under the age of 18-32 which I believe is a huge number when it comes to discovering talent. Inclusion of people with special disabilities will give them an opportunity to learn about the basics and will create employment as well as entrepreneurship activities within this group. 
Our goal with this proposal is to create 12 educational videos geared towards people with special disabilities with a focus on explaining the basics.

Since sign language is globally accepted way of communicating, creating videos in sign language directly opens up our content in multiple countries.

## Value to Synthetix
My goal is to create an entire playlist that walks through all of the basics of Synthetix and make it practical by showcasing everything on a test network. This will make sure that these users are comfortable in carrying out any actions on the networks and can explore the ecosystem with ease.


## Project Implementation Plan
The goal is to release each video on a Sunday so that users have more time to go through the video and read up on the things mentioned in the video. We need three months to cover all the basic videos.


## Additional Information


## Funding Request
We are looking for $7000 USD

description:
This proposal purpose is to have next 3 month Bond allocation to split among Olympus and Maximizer for Protocol owned Liquidity (POL). 
With recent on-chain proposal (Treasury Replenishment Request), entire $500K per month being allocated to bond on Olympus platform. 
Maximizer Platform have recently demonstrated that PNG-AVAX and some other DEX pairs bond have very high demand and they usually get sold out less than 24 hours compared to Olympus, which taken over few weeks to sold out the same amount of Bond sale. 

We do strongly believe having strong collaboration with Avalanche native project like Maximizer will be supremely value added for Pangolin Ecosystem especially to help bootstrapping new projects and onboard them on Pangolin to start their liquidity with and not to chose competitors DEX to start with.
